Sentencas: Several transport models for fuel cells have been developed.
Titulo: Computer methods for performance prediction in fuel cells

Sentencas: The models are compared and tested for single fuel cells and multi-cell stacks of planar solid-oxide fuel cells, the three main approaches considered are (a) a detailed numerical model (DNM) of flow, heat and mass transfer and electrochemistry, (b) a flow-based methodology based on a distributed resistance analogy (DRA), and (c) a presumed-flow methodology (PFM).
Titulo: Computer methods for performance prediction in fuel cells

Sentencas: The results from each of the above approaches are compared in detail, and merits and drawbacks discussed.
Titulo: Computer methods for performance prediction in fuel cells

Sentencas: It is shown that, under certain circumstances, the simpler approaches have the potential to supplant or complement the direct numerical method in the analysis of fuel cells.
Titulo: Computer methods for performance prediction in fuel cells
